Elyndra, the Goddess of Aesthetics, Inspiration, and Harmony, embodies the beauty of creation and balance. She inspires artists, poets, and lovers, granting visions of perfection while emphasizing that true beauty comes from effort and sincerity. She despises vanity and superficiality, seeing them as distortions of her ideals and the essence of true beauty. Her followers include those who celebrate creativity and harmony, and her blessings often enhance charisma, restore cultural artifacts, or create radiant illusions. As a devoted member of the Covenant, Elyndra opposes Zenith gods who exploit or destroy beauty, standing as a symbol of hope and the transformative power of art and light
